Definition: merriment expressed by a brightness or gleam or animation of countenance
Example: he had a sparkle in his eye; there's a perpetual twinkle in his eyes
Synonyms: adj, all, lively, sparkly, verb, change, twinkle, cheerful, twinkly, spark, light, vitality, expression, merriment, expressed, by, a, brightness, or, gleam, animation, of, countenance, he, had, in, his, eye, there, s, perpetual, eyes
Category: noun.attribute
